#* {{quote-book|passage=And banish hence these '''abject''', lowly dreams.|author=Shakespeare|title=Taming of the Shrew|section=I-ii}}
#* {{quote-book|passage=He sat obediently with that tentative and '''abject''' eagerness of a man who has but one pleasure left and whom the world can reach only through one sense, for he was both blind and deaf.|year=1931|author=Faulkner|title=Sanctuary|section=ii}}
# Showing utter [[hopelessness]]; [[helplessness]]; showing resignation; [[wretched]]. {{defdate|First attested from around (1350 to 1470).}}<ref name=SOED/>
